creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
inscription:
Signature, Date, Inscription, Stamp

inscribed in plate at top: [NESSI VESTE RABIDVS SE COMBVRIT HERCVLES / PHILOCRASSES]
markings: brown stamp on verso, lower left: Victor Honig (Lugt 4820)
provenance: Victor Honig (1921-2013), San Francisco; David Tunick, New York; John E. Andrus III, Wayzata, Minn.; by descent to his daughters, Elizabeth, Katie, and Julie. Earlier provenances have been gathered, but further research will increase our knowledge of their histories.
signed: monogram and date in plate at lower right: [1548 / HSB]
title: Death of Hercules, From the Labors of Hercules
